        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 11 at 6:28PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 628 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Farmerville, or 20 miles northeast of Ruston, moving northeast at 15
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Huttig, Farmerville, Marion, Felsenthal, D Arbonne, Bayou D Arbonne
Lake, Cecil, Shiloh, Aurelle, Oakland, and Litroe.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
